http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Valedictory-of-centenary-fete-on-Sunday/article14026081.ece

The valedictory function of the year-long birth centenary celebrations of the sixth Catholicos of the Malankara Orthodox Syrian Church, the late Baselios Marthoma Mathews II will be held at the Saint Thomas Orthodox Cathedral here on January 31. The function, which will be presided over by the present Catholicos Baselios Marthoma Paulose II will be inaugurated by Speaker N. Shakthan.A book on Baselios Marthoma Mathews II will be released by the Metropolitan of the South West American Diocese of the Malankara Orthodox Syrian Church, Alexios Mar Eusebios. The education fund distribution will inaugurated by the Metropolitan of the Kottarakara-Punalur diocese, Yuhanon Mar Thevodorus.A.A. Azeez, MLA, will launch the housing fund assistance of the diocese and Mayor V. Rajendrababu will inaugurate the wedding assistance fund.As a prelude to the function, a procession from the tomb of Baselios Marthoma Mathews II at Mar Elia Chapel Sasthamcotta to the function venue will be held earlier in the day.